<div class="highlight">
<pre><code class="language-html" data-lang="html">
<span class="cp">&lbrace;&lbrace;</span><span class="nv">profile-image</span> <span class="na">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;large&quot;</span> <span class="na">shape</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;square&quot;</span> <span class="na">badgeCount</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="m">18</span> <span class="na">imageSrc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;/img/profiles/emmet.jpg&#39;</span><span class="cp">&rbrace;&rbrace;</span>
<span class="cp">&lbrace;&lbrace;</span><span class="nv">profile-image</span> <span class="na">size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;large&quot;</span> <span class="na">shape</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">&quot;circle&quot;</span> <span class="na">badgeCount</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="m">18</span> <span class="na">imageSrc</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">&#39;/img/profiles/emmet.jpg&#39;</span><span class="cp">&rbrace;&rbrace;</span>
</code></pre></div>

<div class="quote-panel quote-panel-warning" id="profile-image-yield">
    <div class="quote-panel-heading"><h4>Content Yield</h4></div>
    <div class="quote-panel-body">
        <p>Like other components, the Profile Image will yield content. This yielded content will be rendered in a div with the class <code>overlay-container</code>. It will be layered over the image (regular or blurred) and underneath badges. This element is styled to match the dimensions and shape of the underlying profile image.</p>
        <p>By default, yielded content may overflow the bounds of the profile-image. To prevent overflow, add the class <code>no-overflow</code> to the component.</p>
    </div>
</div>
